It's a great machine for anyone who heavily uses the internet, writing articles or creating word documents and Photoshop or Lightroom projects.

I had also accidentally banged the computer against my desk at work while it was in the soft case about a year after I bought it. Thus, there is a slight dent at the top of the ethernet input structure. Apple's Genius Bar on Broadway checked everything out and concluded that it was just cosmetic.  
 
The battery is approx. 3 years old and was replaced at the Ridge Hill Apple Store in Yonkers. 
 
The screen was never cracked, shattered or chipped.

The MacBook Air family is a line of Apple ultraportable Macintosh notebook computers. These computers feature a one piece aluminum razor thin casing and do not include an apical drive to save space and weight. This MacBook Air (MB003LL/A) features a customized 1.6 GHz Intel "Core 2 Duo" processor (P7500) in a miniaturized packaging design with two independent processor "cores" on a single chip with a 4 MB on-chip shared level 2 cache running on an 800 MHz frontside bus and 2 GB of onboard 667 MHz DDR2 SDRAM, an 80 GB PATA (4200 RPM) hard drive, an Intel GMA X3100 integrated "graphics processor with 144 MB of DDR2 SDRAM shared with main memory", an integrated iSight video camera, a "MacBook-style" full-size backlit keyboard with ambient light sensor. The solid aluminum casing houses a 13.3" widescreen TFT LED backlit active-matrix "glossy" display (1280x800 native resolution). Connectivity includes AirPort Extreme (802.11a/b/g/n), Bluetooth 2.1+EDR, a single USB 2.0 port, analog audio out, and video out capabilities (micro-DVI) that support an external 24" display. It lacks Ethernet (an external adapter is available), Firewire, and optical audio in/out.

title: Trade Custom Wood Kayak for - Guitar, Drums, SUP Board, iMac, Macbook
description:
Looking to trade my Kayak for a decent Guitar, Drums, a Tube Amp, a quality SUP board, a Surf Board (longboard!).  Would also trade for an iMac, MacBook Pro, or Mac Mini - (2013 or newer).  If you have something you want to trade, feel free to shoot me the make/model/year info - and photos of it.   
 
My kayak was built completely by me, and so maybe someone out there would enjoy this kind of trade!  The guitar (or other item) should be in good clean condition and not in need major maintenance.   
 
About the kayak: It is like new. I built it from scratch by adapting plans to my own needs. It is plywood built via stitch and glue technique using West Systems Epoxy (best epoxy out there). The entire bottom is covered by a single sheet of fiberglass and all wood is completely coated in epoxy inside and out. It cannot leak unless you drill a hole in it!  Construction is beyond solid. There are foot rests mounted in the cockpit, and a small hatch in the sealed bulkhead behind the seat to provide for some storage. It is designed for someone who is approximately 5'8" and around 190 lbs. Really tall folks will not fit, and really fat ones won't fit either.  If you are shorter or lighter than this, it would work for you for sure. 
 
A front hatch could be added at any time if you want a place to stow other gear.  It tracks very well. All hardware is stainless steel and a kayak skirt is included, but a paddle is not. Interlux exterior grade marine paint and varnish was used. Length is 13' and the design is based on the Mill Creek Kayak from wooden boat magazine. It has forward and rear cleats to run an anchor line through as well as some deck top bungee lines for securing some fishing tackle or a bluetooth radio. 
 
I'm located on Staten Island, NY near Silver Lake Park if you'd like to see it.

title: Super DJ Music Collection 1.8TB
description:
Don't be fool; this is the deal for you, it includes the 2TB Western Digital, Seagate, and Toshiba hard drive available so you are ready to go on any GiG, it will have Hours of Music in each genre.  
 
In this music collection you can be assured that music from all genres are included. With a wide collection that spans from Country to Latin to Jazz to EDM you can be assured that you have what you need for any party. You can be sure that all pop hits all the way to 2016 are available. Even music from countries such as Germany and India are inside this drive. With all this you will be able tackle parties, weddings, or even children parties. This collection is designed so that you will be able to feel like a true DJ and with a collection up to pare.    
 
With remixes, sound effects, and beats you can apply your own touch to classics that will be sure to completely change the energy of a party. Part of this collections job is to provide you with the tools to be able to make sure that your party is truly your own. These tools are modern and well recorded meaning that you will have no problem inserting these into your sets. 
 
Even for the less "energized" parties you can be certain that you the music to power these up. From Birthday songs to Halloween to Christmas songs you can be sure that you have all that you need. More importantly this collection has over 2 TB's of music meaning that if you ever need to take a request you can be almost certain that you will have all that you need. 
 
 
 
 
The compound of a DJ: 
Today's DJ has to know a lot about mashing up, remixing and even producing, to be in any way serious about being a professional. 
Key Factor to being a good enough DJ 
 
Track Selection:  
With the largest professional DJ music collection available. But DJ music isn't enough. Track selection is largely a product of personal taste and your target audience, whereas track order is determined by the energy levels you hope to achieve. 
Order: 
The single most important factor in enabling a DJ to play a genrus out of their confort level. 
Transitions: 
DJ mixes has to have a mixed bag of genres, change it up transition-wise. If you are playing a single genre, like Drum n' Bass, seamless beat matching all the way through is the way to go. description:
Selling my 27" LED Cinema Display. Currently using with my new 2016 MacBook Pro, will be including the USB-C adaptor as well as all of the adaptors I have used with this monitor for different generations of Mac products. Still have the original box as well. 
 
Also including my Satechi Premium Aluminum stand with USB 3.0 Hub. 
 
Connect the 27-inch Apple LED Cinema Display to your Mac and supersize your view with an incredible 2560-by-1440 resolution, LED backlighting for instant-on brightness, and an amazing 178-degree viewing angle.  
 
The LED Cinema Display features a universal MagSafe connector that charges your notebook, a Mini DisplayPort cable for easy connectivity, and three USB 2.0 ports. There's also a built-in iSight camera, microphone, and 49-watt speaker system that provide a true desktop experience.  
 
Made of aluminum and glass, the LED Cinema Display is the perfect companion for the MacBook family.  
 
It's also compatible with Mac desktop computers that have a Mini DisplayPort -- Mac Pro, Mac mini, and iMac. 
 
This is the mini display port version, non-thunderbolt but works basically the same.

title: LOOKING FOR SOME HELP (SERIOUS REPLIES ONLY PLEASE)
description:
Good Afternoon all, 
 
I am in the midst of repairing my credit and I know this is a long shot but- I am looking for someone that may want /be able to help. I will pay interest or be okay with whatever financial arrangements would be decided if someone does decide to help. I am in dire need of a new Apple Macbook!. For school and work and for myself -it has always been a huge tool in my life for the last ten years.I have a very shitty limited smart phone which does not do much for me at all as far as what I need my laptop for and even then I do my best.  I would love to charge one but that is not happening as I am a young single mother trying to repair my credit -this takes time of course . I simply cannot even afford to spend a few hundred dollars or even a hundred or so on a used one right now off of Ebay or Crauigslist. Do not care if its used or an older model just need one ASAP. Is anyone willing to possibly charge one for me? They are as cheap as 150-200 if I get an older used one which would be suffice for now-I do not expect a $1200 computer.You would decide the price range  and of course we can make arrangements /a contract as far as me paying you back as soon as possible.  
 
Please disregard if you are rolling your eyes at this post or want nothing to do with it. I appreciate your time very much so weather you reply or not-thanks for reading and have a great,blessed day! I am no scam artist or dangerous person.Simply giving this a shot. 
 
 
D

title: ATI Radeon HD 4870 for MacPro (2006 - 2010)
description:
This graphics card upgrade kit is designed for, and fully compatible with, all Mac Pro models. (Please note that the Mac Pro is Apple's desktop tower; this kit is not compatible with the Macbook Pro.)  
 
Simply install this card into one of your Mac Pro's available expansion slots, plug in the two included power cables, and you're done! No drivers are required to run this card on your Mac.  
 
-Fully working OS X boot screen, just like the original Apple card 
-2 DVI ports: 1 dual-link (2560x1600), 1 single-link (1920x1200) 
-Analog (VGA) monitors are not supported 
-OS X 10.5.7 or later is required

title: Recording Mixing & Mastering High End Audio Chain
description:
Hello, offering musical artists & bands a professional recording, mixing & mastering environment using a high end analog signal chain with special attention to quality service & cost effectiveness featuring high end classic analog gear components & converters in addition to a full array of pluggins. My current set up is ideal if you want to record a single or album. Also, if you have live or studio recordings you want to have mastered or mixed or you want your individual instruments such as drum bus, guitar bus, or anything else run through the rig to give your music analog warmth, attitude, thrust or presence. Rates are extremely low at $25 per hour so feel free to contact me & we can discuss the needs of your project.  
 
I've been in business for over 15 years and received my audio engineer certification through IAR (Institute Of Audio Research) and have loads of experience recording, editing, mixing & mastering professional projects from many musical genres. I've focused on Indie Rock, Hard Rock, Funk, Hip-Hop, Singer Song Writer, R&B, Pop & Jazz over the years & love "making it happen" for my artists. The studio front end rivals studios charging $75 to $100 per hour. Below is more info about my audio chain, services & philosoghy. 
 
I have enthusiastically assembled analog outboard gear & an audio signal path which provides rich harmonic content, greatly improving over the typical present day sterile "in the box" digital environment. Something special happens to a signal when you run it through quality high end gear like stereo matched BAE Neve 1084's with complex circuitry, then to additional analog gear with yet more circuitry such as analog EQ's & compressors then finally to analog, transformer based converters which can be cranked up. The result is texture & harmonic content, more complex & rich with a robust wave-train that sits beautifully in the mix evoking an emotional & highly musical response.  
 
For many decades & before the digital recording era, engineers used complex circuitry in their signal path to capture the emotional content of their artists work. This includes the tape machine which in addition to magnetic tape qualities also has its own complex circuitry. Since the digital revolution, many audio engineers I continue to learn from have been trying to overcome the sterile & less emotional digital realm by using a combination of old school, classic outboard gear coupled with converters that emulate tape machines. In my experience, the classic analog outboard gear components & Burl converters with hand made transformers offer a true bridge in this "here to stay" digital era to achieve the type of audio performance & results associated with that old school quality analog sound. 
 
Outboard Gear List  
Brooklyn Bull Recording Studio 
 
BAE Neve 1084 Stereo Pair: Probably one of the nicer line level capable mic pre amps in the recording industry. So many tones & colors available driving them hot or cold, handling balanced & unbalanced signal as well as mic'ed signals. Great for providing attitude to electric guitars, drums & vocals etc. They can also run cooler providing a more transparent representation of the source. They sit in the mix beautifully & when the stereo pair is used on the summing amp, their circuitry provides weight, depth, imaging & natural compression. 
 
Burl B2 Bomber ADC Stereo Audio To Digital Converter: This is more of an amazing "tone machine" with input transformers which successfully emulate analog 2" tape when driven hard. This piece of gear is a true game changer as we can finally overcome the sterile digital world and achieve fat & rich harmonics associated with the analog world circuitry from the golden age of recording. Many options are available to use this piece of gear during recording, mixing & mastering.  
 
API 5500 Stereo or Dual Mono EQ: Known for its signature API forward analog sound, it delivers while tracking, mixing or mastering. A must have & great compliment to the other API gear in the rack. 
 
API 2500 Stereo Compressor:  
Great for tracking, bus mix, final mix & mastering. Adds thrust & attitude to any signal or runs clean to provide body & presence & can be run coupled in stereo or dual mono. It's reputation speaks for itself; a very exciting piece of gear used in major recording & mastering studios around the world. 
 
API 3124+ Mic Preamps: Vintage circuitry with a highly musical & modern sound. Big yet contained bottom yields a really fat sound and these pre amps are highly flexible run cool or hot to bring out harmonic content most effectively used in conjunction with various in house EQ's & compressors. 
 
Avalon 747 Stereo Compressor & EQ: Truly glues a mix together & has a musical EQ with optional tube signal path. Known for it's highly musical yet transparent qualities, everything sounds better running through the 747 including bus mixes, final mixes & mastering. It also shines in many tracking situations such as mono or stereo keyboards, drum machines, overheads etc. 
 
Teletronix La2a Compressor: 
Simply put, it's an incredible "tone machine" whether the signal is barely being processed or the La2a is aggressively grabbing the signal, this classic brings out harmonic content & wave-train like nothing else & proudly sits in every high end studio. 
 
Purple MC77 Compressor: 
Crafted by good guys who are locals in the Nyc area, they made a tank of a device modeled after the famous classic Universal Audio 1176 & did a better job! I Use it in about every tracking & mixing session.  
 
Chandler TG2 Abby Road Limited Edition Dual Mic Pre Amp: 
A beast of a musical pre amp designed with the original specs from Abby Road Studios emulating the sounds of The Beatles to Pink Floyd. Runs hot or cold for a transparent effect or major color, mojo & tone. This dual mono or stereo mic pre amp used in tandem with various in house compressors & EQ's really takes tracking to the next level. 
 
Avalon 737 Pre Amp Strip: 
2 rack space classic which shines on many sources including bass, acoustic guitar, vocals, kick & snare etc. Has brand new matched tubes from Avalon & in top form featuring EQ, compression & tube signal path with a very musical & transparent effect. 
 
Universal Audio 6176 Strip. Another 2 rack space classic strip in major studios which does everything the Avalon 737 does but with more of a colored vintage vibe. It delivers modern & relevant tones with old school attitude. The pre amp & compressor can be decoupled for many creative processing options used with other gear. Incredible on vocals, bass, acoustic guitar and the list goes on. 
 
Switchcraft 9625 Patchbay: This is a game changing routing hub for engineers, improving workflow & creativity which is as exciting as any other piece of gear in the studio. Putting many pieces of gear in line in seconds provides an array of creative possibilities allowing for quick access to standard routing as well as unconventional "outside the box" creative combinations. 
 
Dynaudio Acoustic Active Monitoring System: 
Incredible Bm5a Monitors with a matched Bm9s Subwoofer to create mixes that reveal & unmask the lows & lower mid range which often get lost & muddled when mixing without access to the all important lower frequencies.  
 
Microphones: Sennheisser MD 421's, Shure SM57's, Stereo Pair vintage AKG C 414 B-ULS, Neumann U-87ai, vintage Sennheisser MD 441 N, Shure B52, Audio Technica 4033  
 
Running Cubase 8.5 Pro with a full array of plugins such as Waves & UAD's on a new MacBook Pro with a Universal Audio Apollo 16 mkii interface.

Rich Lexicon Reverbs with Plug-in Convenience! 
Lexicon is noted for reverbs, and now the new MX400 and MX400XL dual stereo/surround reverb processors. bring those quality sounds to project studios, surround facilities on a budget, and live sound applications. The new single-rackspace, 4-in, 4-out MX400 combines an intuitive front-panel design with Lexicon's "Hardware Plug-in" technology, a unique USB connection, and an interface for use with software recording platforms. 
 
Lexicon MX400 Dual Stereo/Surround Reverb Processor at a Glance:

The MX400 series also offers an affordable entry into the ever-expanding world of surround applications. Equally at home for live applications, the MX400 supplies the FOH/live sound engineer intuitive front panel control with a backlit LCD screen for parameter displays. A 4-in, 4-out design, the MX400 series offer unprecedented connectivity through TRS balanced I/O (MX400), or XLR I/O (MX400XL). Both products also offer 4-channel surround algorithms, making them an extremely affordable offering to surround mixing facilities.

description:
Hi i have for sale my old  Klark Teknik DN360 EQ Dual Channel 1/3 Octave Graphic Equaliser for 399$ CASH ONLY

Crest Audio X 20R 
DBX DriveRack PX 
 
please text me at 
  
 
 
 
 
The DN360 from Klark Teknik is a dual-channel, thirty-band graphic equalizer, designed and engineered to high standards, enabling the EQ to withstand the rigors of continuous road use. All units also share a sonic consistency, allowing engineers all over the world to replicate settings on locally sourced machines. 
Accurate operation is achieved using the oil damped 30mm faders. These can be set for either +/-6dB or +/-12dB boost and cut. Sub-sonic filters on each channel help protect speakers and amplifiers, and a bypass function provides easy comparison between equalized and direct signals. Overload LEDs indicate problem levels. 
The unit utilizes proportional-Q filtering, which varies the "Q" value depending on the depth of either the cut or boost of a particular band. This results in a "smooth" and "musical" response, while still preserving the original source material. 
Dual-channel, 30-band 1/3 octave graphic equalizer with 30mm oil damped faders 
Covers ISO frequencies between 25Hz and 20kHz 
Scale switching provides the choice of either high fader resolution (+/-6dB) or normal (+/-12dB) 
A low-cut, 18dB/octave filter on each channel prevents subsonic components in the program material from overloading speakers or amplifiers 
Equalization by-pass allows easy comparison between direct and equalized signals 
Earth lift switch enables signal and chassis grounds to be isolated, eliminating ground-loop problems 
Electronically balanced inputs 
LED overload indicators

title: Apple 27" Thunderbolt Display
description:
For sale is an Apple 27" Thunderbolt Display.  
 
I purchased this display about three years ago from the Apple Store in Ann Arbor, Michigan, while I was a law student at U of M. I have used it primarily as a dock for my MacBook Pro, which is a great feature as it transforms a laptop into a makeshift desktop. The screen is massive, so it significantly expands your ability to work with multiple windows or applications open simultaneously. 
 
The display is basically mint condition, as it has been sitting atop my desk since the day I purchased it. It has no scratches, dings, dents, etc. Further, it is in perfect working condition and has never given me any functional problems whatsoever.  
 
Brand new this display was priced at over $1,000 with tax. 
 
Price: $500 
 
Buyer will need to pick up from my doorman apartment in Battery Park City, as the size of the display doesn't lend itself to an exchange at a nearby coffee shop.

title: CANON PIXMA PRO 100 5d t5 t6i rebel eos canon
description:
HEY THERE, 
 
I have a brand new Canon PIXMA Pro 100 Wireless Professional Inkjet Photo Printer $200 or best offer. Picked up in the Bronx.  
 
The printer is brand new and unopened in the box.  
 
Please note that UPC have been carefully cut from both boxes for rebate purposes. 
 
Thank you 
 
 
============================================================ 
Canon PIXMA PRO-100 Wireless Professional Inkjet Photo Printer features a 4800 x 2400 dpi resolution and Canon's FINE technology with an ink drop as small as 3.0 pl. The printer's 8-cartridge ink system provides a wide color range and includes 3 black inks for high-quality black-and-white photos. The Pro-100 can output borderless prints up to 13 x 19" and is compatible with a wide range of media, including glossy, luster, and matte photo paper as well as Museum Etching and other fine art papers. Additionally, you can print directly on CDs, DVDs, and Blu-ray discs and create your own customizable discs and jackets. The included Print Studio Pro plug in software provides an easy way to achieve optimal results when printing directly from Adobe Photoshop CS and Elements, as well as from Adobe Photoshop Lightroom. 
 
The PIXMA Pro-100 features multiple connectivity options so you can easily print from your different devices. In addition to a standard USB connection, you can connect to the printer over a wired or wireless Ethernet network. Additionally, you can use the front-facing USB port to print directly from a compatible digital camera with PictBridge compatibility. 
 
The PictBridge cable is not included 
 
Print Speeds 
Print an 8.0x10" image in approximately 51 seconds and an 11x14" image in approximately 1 minute 30 seconds 
Canon FINE Technology 
Canon Full-photolithography Inkjet Nozzle Engineering (FINE) features a patented print head that enables printing with microscopic droplets and high resolution up to 4800 x 2400 dpi 
True Monochrome Prints 
The 3 monochrome inks which are part of the 8-ink ChromaLife 100+ system consist of Black, Gray, and Light Gray. These inks deliver enhanced, deep black density to raise your level of professional print quality when creating the dramatic expression of grayscale photography 
Optimum Analysis & Mixture Of Color 
The Optimum Image Generating (OIG) System utilizes two major technologies that were first introduced in the PIXMA PRO-1. The first is a sophisticated mixing balance of inks determined from numerous ink combinations and advanced analysis. During this analysis, the OIG System carefully calculates the best results for each print mode and paper type used while looking at various image factors including color reproduction, tonal gradations, black density, low graininess, glossiness, anti-bronzing and anti-metamerism. These critical ink balancing principles are derived from Canon's expertise in imaging technology, as well as the familiar colors of life that people see and remember on a daily basis. The second is the balancing of color reproduction, tonal gradations, and uniform glossiness. The genius and power of the OIG System is truly showcased when your image is printed, exhibited, and is seen exactly as you envisioned it 
Pro Printing 
The powerful Print Studio Pro plug-in software provides professional photographers effective printing solutions and can directly hand-over image data. Print Studio Pro is compatible with Digital Photo Professional (ver. 2.1 or later), Adobe Photoshop CS, Photoshop Elements, and Photoshop Lightroom 
Built-In CD & DVD Printing 
Conveniently print onto your printable CD, DVD or Blu-ray discs and jackets 
Print Your Vision Up To 13x19" 
Print professional quality photos on various media up to 13x19" 
Versatile Paper Handling 
The 2-way paper feeding provides a rear tray for most supported media types and a dedicated manual feed in the back of the printer for easy loading of thicker papers 
Built-In Wi-Fi 
The built-in Wi-Fi gives you the freedom to place the printer where it's convenient and allows multiple users to seamlessly print from several computers 
Built-in Ethernet Connectivity 
The built-in Ethernet port allows multiple users to seamlessly print from several networked computers in any environment 
Computer-Free Printing 
PictBridge lets you print photos directly from your compatible digital camera, DV camcorder, or camera phone 
Hi-Speed USB 
Plug the cable into your PC for fast data transfer 
AirPrint 
Print photos, email, Web pages and documents from a MacBook, iPhone, iPad, or iPod Touch directly to your printer without installing a driver

title: apple usb hdmi adaptor   USB-C HDMI
description:
New sealed in original box 
 
 
The USB-C Digital AV Multiport Adapter lets you connect your MacBook with USB-C port or MacBook Pro with Thunderbolt 3 (USB-C) ports to an HDMI display, while also connecting a standard USB device and a USB-C charging cable. 
This adapter allows you to mirror your MacBook or MacBook Pro display to your HDMI-enabled TV or display in up to 1080p at 60Hz or UHD (3840 by 2160) at 30Hz. It also outputs video content like movies and captured video. Simply connect the adapter to the USB-C port on your MacBook or any of the Thunderbolt 3 (USB-C) ports on your MacBook Pro and then to your TV or projector via an HDMI cable (sold separately). 
Use the standard USB port to connect devices such as your flash drive or camera or a USB cable for syncing and charging your iPhone, iPad, or iPod. You can also connect a charging cable to the USB-C port to charge your MacBook or MacBook Pro. 
Note: The Apple USB-C Digital AV Multiport Adapter is not compatible with the G-Tech G-DRIVE mobile USB 3.0 Hard Drive (Apple part number HF4F2VC/A)

I'm selling my Elgato Thunderbolt 2 Dock for $150 (retail price is $200).   It includes a 6ft Apple Thunderbolt to Thunderbolt cable (pictured, retail $40) and a 6ft Amazon Basic Thunderbolt to DisplayPort cable (not pictured, retail $10). 
 
Other than some scratches around the ports, the dock is in excellent condition.  I'm selling it because I bought a proper desktop and don't need it for my MBP anymore.  It includes the following ports: 
 
- 2 x Thunderbolt 2 
- 1 x HDMI 1.4b output 
- 1 x RJ45 Gigabit Ethernet 
- 3 x USB 3.0 
- 1 x 3.5 Millimeter headphone output 
- 1 x 3.5 Millimeter microphone input 
- 1 x Power input 
 
Several Thunderbolt docks are very quirky/flaky, I never had any problems with this one.  It just worked.  My configuration was: 
 
- MacBook Pro 
- 29" 4k LG 
- 21" 2k LG 
- Ethernet over the dock  
- A few different devices on the USB 3.0 ports (including hard drives and flash card readers). 
 
*** Please note that it will only drive one 4K monitor and one 2K monitor at the same time, it won't drive two 4K monitors.  (I was using it with an LG 4K and LG 2K with no issues).  The 4K monitor has to be over Thunderbolt/DisplayPort, which is why I'm including the cable.  You can't drive 4K over the HDMI port. 
 
*** Cash/Venmo only 
*** In person exchanges only

title: Apple LED Cinema Display 24-Inch MB382LL/A
description:
This monitor is 100% clean and working great. The screen has no scratches. Bought a new 4K display so no longer need it. Please see photos attached of the real, actual monitor (not stock images). The base has a small ding in it but has no effect on the display whatsoever (see pictures). 
 
24-inch (viewable) LED-backlit thin film transistor (TFT) active-matrix liquid crystal display. 
Supported resolutions: 1920 by 1200 pixels 1280 by 800 pixels 1024 by 640 pixels 
Compatible with MacBook, MacBook Air, and MacBook Pro systems with Mini DisplayPort 
Three connectors: Mini DisplayPort, MagSafe, USB 
Three self-powered USB 2.0 ports.  
Built-in iSight camera with microphone.  
Built-in 2.1 speaker system. 
 
The first display made precisely for a MacBook. The new 24-inch Apple LED Cinema Display doesnt just expand the screen of your new MacBook, MacBook Pro, or MacBook Air, it expands your whole experience. Plug in three simple connectors on one cable the new industry-standard Mini DisplayPort, MagSafe, and USB and suddenly you have more room to work and play, power for your notebook, and access to peripherals. The built-in iSight camera, microphone, and speaker system let you video chat or listen to your music whether your MacBook is open or closed. And it features a mercury-free LED-backlit display that delivers stunning 1920-by-1200-pixel resolution. With the LED Cinema Display, everything you see is bigger, brighter, and even more brilliant. Video chatting requires a broadband Internet connection; fees may apply.

description:
For the Music Producer or Future Music Producer in your life, here's what I have for Trade:  
 
Brand New in The Box 2016 Akai Professional MPC Studio Reboot in Black, will come with a use Roland PC-180 Midi Controller, and Two Mics; ones a Vintage Astatic Model D-104 Microphone and the other is a Samson C01 Large-Diaphragm Studio Condenser Microphone! 
 
MPC Studio Black: 
At under one-inch thin, with low-profile controls and a brushed aluminum body, MPC Studio made to move. MPC Studio merges real MPC pads, iconic workflow, and the same MPC Software used by MPC Renaissance to give you a fully integrated portable production solution. Welcome to production anywhere. The world is now your studio. - Legendary MPC Production on Your PC or Mac - The MPC Studio Music Production Controller fuses legendary MPC production with the processing power of your computer. Its compact design is less than 1" thin and fits easily into a laptop bag or backpack. It's USB-powered with low-profile knobs and brushed aluminum body, and includes MPC Software for Mac and PC with 128-track sequencing capability. With 16 backlit genuine MPC pads, legendary MPC workflow, MPC Swing, plus four touch-sensitive knobs providing enhanced MPC software control, you'll be producing quality music in no time. A large LCD screen (360 x 96 dot graphic LCD) allows you to make tracks without having to look at your computer. - Featuring 128-track sequencing capability and up to eight pad banks--more than any other MPC everthe included MPC Software delivers a massive 7GB+ sound library, including all the sounds of the classic MPC3000 and 2 MPC Expansions. Instant mapping and real-time adjustment of VST plugins lets you record each track as an MPC drum program, Keygroup program, or VST/AU plug-in. Use MPC Software alone as your main DAW, or use it seamlessly with your current studio as a VST, RTAS, or AU plugin. - MPC Software supports WAV, MP3, AIFF, REX, and SND, as well as samples and sequences from any MPC ever made, and it's compatible with both Mac and PC.It's all in The Bank7 Gigabytes. 300 Instruments. The Bank is an included MPC Expansion workstation loaded with essential sounds of modern production including basses, leads, effects, keyboards and much more. title: CANON PIXMA PRO 100 5d t5 t6i rebel eos canon
description:
HEY THERE, 
 
I have a brand new Canon PIXMA Pro 100 Wireless Professional Inkjet Photo Printer $200 or best offer. Picked up in the Bronx.  
 
The printer is brand new and unopened in the box.  
 
Please note that UPC have been carefully cut from both boxes for rebate purposes. 
 
Thank you 
 
 
============================================================ 
Canon PIXMA PRO-100 Wireless Professional Inkjet Photo Printer features a 4800 x 2400 dpi resolution and Canon's FINE technology with an ink drop as small as 3.0 pl. The printer's 8-cartridge ink system provides a wide color range and includes 3 black inks for high-quality black-and-white photos. The Pro-100 can output borderless prints up to 13 x 19" and is compatible with a wide range of media, including glossy, luster, and matte photo paper as well as Museum Etching and other fine art papers. Additionally, you can print directly on CDs, DVDs, and Blu-ray discs and create your own customizable discs and jackets. The included Print Studio Pro plug in software provides an easy way to achieve optimal results when printing directly from Adobe Photoshop CS and Elements, as well as from Adobe Photoshop Lightroom. 
 
The PIXMA Pro-100 features multiple connectivity options so you can easily print from your different devices. In addition to a standard USB connection, you can connect to the printer over a wired or wireless Ethernet network. Additionally, you can use the front-facing USB port to print directly from a compatible digital camera with PictBridge compatibility. 
 
The PictBridge cable is not included 
 
Print Speeds 
Print an 8.0x10" image in approximately 51 seconds and an 11x14" image in approximately 1 minute 30 seconds 
Canon FINE Technology 
Canon Full-photolithography Inkjet Nozzle Engineering (FINE) features a patented print head that enables printing with microscopic droplets and high resolution up to 4800 x 2400 dpi 
True Monochrome Prints 
The 3 monochrome inks which are part of the 8-ink ChromaLife 100+ system consist of Black, Gray, and Light Gray. These inks deliver enhanced, deep black density to raise your level of professional print quality when creating the dramatic expression of grayscale photography 
Optimum Analysis & Mixture Of Color 
The Optimum Image Generating (OIG) System utilizes two major technologies that were first introduced in the PIXMA PRO-1. The first is a sophisticated mixing balance of inks determined from numerous ink combinations and advanced analysis. During this analysis, the OIG System carefully calculates the best results for each print mode and paper type used while looking at various image factors including color reproduction, tonal gradations, black density, low graininess, glossiness, anti-bronzing and anti-metamerism. These critical ink balancing principles are derived from Canon's expertise in imaging technology, as well as the familiar colors of life that people see and remember on a daily basis. The second is the balancing of color reproduction, tonal gradations, and uniform glossiness. The genius and power of the OIG System is truly showcased when your image is printed, exhibited, and is seen exactly as you envisioned it 
Pro Printing 
The powerful Print Studio Pro plug-in software provides professional photographers effective printing solutions and can directly hand-over image data. Print Studio Pro is compatible with Digital Photo Professional (ver. 2.1 or later), Adobe Photoshop CS, Photoshop Elements, and Photoshop Lightroom 
Built-In CD & DVD Printing 
Conveniently print onto your printable CD, DVD or Blu-ray discs and jackets 
Print Your Vision Up To 13x19" 
Print professional quality photos on various media up to 13x19" 
Versatile Paper Handling 
The 2-way paper feeding provides a rear tray for most supported media types and a dedicated manual feed in the back of the printer for easy loading of thicker papers 
Built-In Wi-Fi 
The built-in Wi-Fi gives you the freedom to place the printer where it's convenient and allows multiple users to seamlessly print from several computers 
Built-in Ethernet Connectivity 
The built-in Ethernet port allows multiple users to seamlessly print from several networked computers in any environment 
Computer-Free Printing 
PictBridge lets you print photos directly from your compatible digital camera, DV camcorder, or camera phone 
Hi-Speed USB 
Plug the cable into your PC for fast data transfer 
AirPrint 
Print photos, email, Web pages and documents from a MacBook, iPhone, iPad, or iPod Touch directly to your printer without installing a driver

title: caNON PIXMA PRO 100 5d t5 t6i rebel eos canon
description:
HEY THERE, 
 
I have a brand new Canon PIXMA Pro 100 Wireless Professional Inkjet Photo Printer $200 or best offer. Picked up in the Bronx.  
 
The printer is brand new and unopened in the box.  
 
Please note that UPC have been carefully cut from both boxes for rebate purposes. 
 
Thank you 
 
 
============================================================ 
Canon PIXMA PRO-100 Wireless Professional Inkjet Photo Printer features a 4800 x 2400 dpi resolution and Canon's FINE technology with an ink drop as small as 3.0 pl. The printer's 8-cartridge ink system provides a wide color range and includes 3 black inks for high-quality black-and-white photos. The Pro-100 can output borderless prints up to 13 x 19" and is compatible with a wide range of media, including glossy, luster, and matte photo paper as well as Museum Etching and other fine art papers. Additionally, you can print directly on CDs, DVDs, and Blu-ray discs and create your own customizable discs and jackets. The included Print Studio Pro plug in software provides an easy way to achieve optimal results when printing directly from Adobe Photoshop CS and Elements, as well as from Adobe Photoshop Lightroom. 
 
The PIXMA Pro-100 features multiple connectivity options so you can easily print from your different devices. In addition to a standard USB connection, you can connect to the printer over a wired or wireless Ethernet network. Additionally, you can use the front-facing USB port to print directly from a compatible digital camera with PictBridge compatibility. 
 
The PictBridge cable is not included 
 
Print Speeds 
Print an 8.0x10" image in approximately 51 seconds and an 11x14" image in approximately 1 minute 30 seconds 
Canon FINE Technology 
Canon Full-photolithography Inkjet Nozzle Engineering (FINE) features a patented print head that enables printing with microscopic droplets and high resolution up to 4800 x 2400 dpi 
True Monochrome Prints 
The 3 monochrome inks which are part of the 8-ink ChromaLife 100+ system consist of Black, Gray, and Light Gray. These inks deliver enhanced, deep black density to raise your level of professional print quality when creating the dramatic expression of grayscale photography 
Optimum Analysis & Mixture Of Color 
The Optimum Image Generating (OIG) System utilizes two major technologies that were first introduced in the PIXMA PRO-1. The first is a sophisticated mixing balance of inks determined from numerous ink combinations and advanced analysis. During this analysis, the OIG System carefully calculates the best results for each print mode and paper type used while looking at various image factors including color reproduction, tonal gradations, black density, low graininess, glossiness, anti-bronzing and anti-metamerism. These critical ink balancing principles are derived from Canon's expertise in imaging technology, as well as the familiar colors of life that people see and remember on a daily basis. The second is the balancing of color reproduction, tonal gradations, and uniform glossiness. The genius and power of the OIG System is truly showcased when your image is printed, exhibited, and is seen exactly as you envisioned it 
Pro Printing 
The powerful Print Studio Pro plug-in software provides professional photographers effective printing solutions and can directly hand-over image data. Print Studio Pro is compatible with Digital Photo Professional (ver. 2.1 or later), Adobe Photoshop CS, Photoshop Elements, and Photoshop Lightroom 
Built-In CD & DVD Printing 
Conveniently print onto your printable CD, DVD or Blu-ray discs and jackets 
Print Your Vision Up To 13x19" 
Print professional quality photos on various media up to 13x19" 
Versatile Paper Handling 
The 2-way paper feeding provides a rear tray for most supported media types and a dedicated manual feed in the back of the printer for easy loading of thicker papers 
Built-In Wi-Fi 
The built-in Wi-Fi gives you the freedom to place the printer where it's convenient and allows multiple users to seamlessly print from several computers 
Built-in Ethernet Connectivity 
The built-in Ethernet port allows multiple users to seamlessly print from several networked computers in any environment 
Computer-Free Printing 
PictBridge lets you print photos directly from your compatible digital camera, DV camcorder, or camera phone 
Hi-Speed USB 
Plug the cable into your PC for fast data transfer 
AirPrint 
Print photos, email, Web pages and documents from a MacBook, iPhone, iPad, or iPod Touch directly to your printer without installing a driver

title: Conran's rolling computer desk elegant black metal
description:
Conran's rolling black metal computer desk/cart/workstation elegant  
From the 1990s; purchased at Sir Terrance Conran's midtown store. 
 
Vintage, but a flexible and timeless design that has proven very useful with  
  many generations & form factors of Macs (These old photos show an eMac, 
     but over the years the desk has been used with iBook, MacBook Air, Mac Minis,  
       as well as 24" and 27' screen iMacs. 
 
Robust, rugged solidly-built design. 
 
Compact 24 by 30 inch footprint takes up minimal space  
   and means desk may easily be rolled through a doorway to another room 
It's also portable in another sense: it is easy to disassemble, move to another location, and reassemble.  
 
All shelves, including the keyboard shelf, are 26" x 15", providing lots of room  
    for printer/scanner/back-up drives/monitor/speakers/soundbar etc. 
 
The keyboard shelf slides back when not in use.

Improved Multi Sample Anti-Aliasing MSAA Technology 
 
Smooth lines is the difference between bitty low quality graphics to a smooth realistic graphics. 
 
MSAA smoothes out the jagged edges of a curved object. A black curved line on a white background displayed on a computer screen will have some jaggedness along its edges due to the inherent limitations of using discrete pixels to display the image. Anti-aliasing smoothes out this jaggedness by filling in the white spaces between the jagged edges with varying shades of grey which gives you the smooth soft shadows, crisp sharp lines of buildings, and crisp tiny details in clothing that make your experience truely realistic.

description:
This is a VG/NEAR-mint condition, functionally restored TEAC 7030 GSL 1/4" professional reel to reel   deck from an estate sale. It was apparently purchased and either only used once or twice or perhaps even never used. I was told by the restorer of this deck that it was the cleanest deck of any kind, any brand, any age he had ever opened up. He told me it was so freakishly clean inside that he felt like he was in a time warp or the twilight zone while servicing the deck. 
 
I do not have any 1/4" reel to reel tapes of any kind to play on this deck right now, but I will do my best to set up the deck for you to record from a CD onto a virgin quarter inch reel. I do not have any prerecorded tapes to demonstrate this deck because of the following logistic:  . Please bring your own 7 1/2 ips or 15 ips 2 track master quality recordings if you want to hear accurate playback on this deck.  . If you don't know what I mean by this, either research what I just said or you have absolutely no business considering the purchase of this deck. Thanks in advance! 
 
I worked in the music business and artist management fields for 7 years and prior to that, I studied audio engineering and production for 2 years. I am an educated seller with a strong knowledge of  the approximate value and extreme rarity of this unit. I will wait for the right buyer who knows exactly what this deck is and what it is not. Perhaps a local recording studio or audio restoration house might be interested. 
 
Because this deck has been sitting in a (clean) closet for the past 6-7 years, you will want to have it professionally recalibrated or at least properly cleaned and demagnitized before recording or playing any tapes. Please also note/remember that any older tapes you intend to play on this deck may need to be baked first.  Thanks again, in advance!

- 1/4" high, low tape speeds (15, 7.5 IPS)

- 2 and 4 track operation

- Tape mon / Source selector 
- Multiple 2-track record features 
- EQ high, normal 
- High, normal bias 
- Includes reel adapters for larger professional studio formats (not pictured -- email with any questions and I can send pics of adapters and accessories that are included with the purchase of this deck)

Photojojo Magnetic iPhone and Android Lens Set And Pouch 
 
- NEW!

- Fisheye, Super Fisheye, Telephoto, Wide Angle, Macro and Polarizing cell phone lenses. 
- Convenient Protective Carrying Case keeps all of your lenses in one safe place. 
 
It's hard to believe you were once inseparable from your fancy bag of camera equipment. Now you take more photos with your phone than your 5D Mark III. Sadly, its lens is far from L Series. 
 
You're in luck. Our iPhone and Android Lens Series is like a set of pro-lenses for your phone! 
 
Each lens is crafted out of solid aluminum and outfitted with thick, high-clarity glass. They've been factory tested by hand and inspected to ensure the utmost optical perfection. Android phone lens, iPhone lens, iPod Touch, iPad, Blackberry, MacBook ... our lenses work with any phone or device that has a lens on it, even if you use a case. 
 
How it works: each set comes with an adhesive removable metal ring that fits any phone and/or a metal Magplate that's specifically cut to camouflage on the back of your iPhone. title: Apple 27" LED Cinema Display Monitor w/ USB 3.0 Stand
description:
Selling my 27" LED Cinema Display. Currently using with my new 2016 MacBook Pro, will be including the USB-C adaptor as well as all of the adaptors I have used with this monitor for different generations of Mac products. Still have the original box as well. 
 
Also including my Satechi Premium Aluminum stand with USB 3.0 Hub. 
 
Connect the 27-inch Apple LED Cinema Display to your Mac and supersize your view with an incredible 2560-by-1440 resolution, LED backlighting for instant-on brightness, and an amazing 178-degree viewing angle.  
 
The LED Cinema Display features a universal MagSafe connector that charges your notebook, a Mini DisplayPort cable for easy connectivity, and three USB 2.0 ports. There's also a built-in iSight camera, microphone, and 49-watt speaker system that provide a true desktop experience.  
 
Made of aluminum and glass, the LED Cinema Display is the perfect companion for the MacBook family.  
 
It's also compatible with Mac desktop computers that have a Mini DisplayPort -- Mac Pro, Mac mini, and iMac. 
 
This is the mini display port version, non-thunderbolt but works basically the same.
attributes: like new Apple 27" LED Cinema Display Monitor

The MacBook "Late 2006 Core 2 Duo" series shares the same easy to upgrade case design as the original MacBook models, and connectivity likewise includes AirPort Extreme (although the "Late 2006" models support 802.11n -- as well as 802.11g -- after a firmware upgrade), Bluetooth 2.0+EDR, Gigabit Ethernet, a FireWire "400" port, two USB 2.0 ports, optical digital audio in/out, and video out capabilities (mini-DVI) that supports an external display. 
 
The MacBook "Late 2006 Core 2 Duo" and original "Core Duo" models also share the same "scrolling TrackPad", built-in iSight video camera, Apple Remote for use with Apple Front Row software, "MagSafe" power connector, "flush against the bed" keyboard that does not touch the screen, and "no moving parts" magnetic latch that "catches without a catch".
